FBIS4-19630 "drweu077_h_94004" FBIS-WEU-94-077 Daily Report 19 Apr 1994 GERMANY Envoy Criticizes Anti-Turkish TV Envoy Criticizes Anti-Turkish TV TA1904200094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1540 GMT 19 Apr 94 TA1904200094 Ankara ANATOLIA English BFN [Text] Bonn, Germany April 09 (A.A.) -- Turkish ambassador to Germany Onur Oymen said today that the friendly feelings of Turks are being damaged continuously by the German media. Speaking at a "roundtable meeting" led by Chancellor Helmut Kohl and which aimed at preventing xenophobia, Oymen said that a number of German TV stations broadcast anti-Turkish programs. Oymen said that 2 million Turks were living in this country and the programs against their homeland hurt their feelings. "These broadcasts are one-sided and the same old archive films are shown again and again, hurting the pride of Turks," he said.
